        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "DOMAIN",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "The extracellular N-terminus has 4 domains; the first 3 are structurally similar to fusogens from plants, C.elegans and viruses, while the fourth domain is unique to archaea. Domains I and II are discontinuous. The fusion loop in domain II is stabilized by a Ca(2+) ion so that it protrudes from the molecule"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "FUNCTION",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Exhibits fusogenic activity, mediates cell-cell fusion when present in both cells (bilateral fusion)"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "SUBCELLULAR LOCATION",
